{{Youmay|the Old Ones that included [[Abeloth]]|the [[Kathol (species)|Kathol]] species, referred to by [[DarkStryder]] as the "Old Ones"}}
{{Quote|You can't kill her, Luke. She's one of the Old Ones.''"<br />"''It doesn't matter what she is.|Mara Jade and Luke Skywalker, regarding Abeloth|<ref name="Apocalypse">''[[Fate of the Jedi: Apocalypse]]''</ref>}}
In the realm [[beyond shadows]], the [[Death/Legends|dead]] spirit of [[Mara Jade Skywalker|Mara Jade]] told [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] that the entity [[Abeloth]] was one of the '''Old Ones''', warning him that the being [[Immortality/Legends|could not be killed]]. Abeloth's immortality resulted from her defying the [[Father (Mortis)/Legends|Father]] of the family [[The Ones/Legends|the Ones]] whom she initially served when they materialized from being [[Celestial/Legends|Celestials]] and then became the Mother; she wanted to be immortal like the rest of her family and thus drank from the [[Font of Power]] and swam in the [[Pool of Knowledge]].<ref name="Apocalypse" /> The [[sinuous carvings]] associated with Abeloth<ref name="Vortex">''[[Fate of the Jedi: Vortex]]''</ref> existed on [[Shatuun]] in the [[Kathol Outback/Legends|Kathol Outback]].<ref name="Warfare Celestials">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-the-essential-guide-to-warfare-authors-cut-the-celestials|text=''Star Wars: The Essential Guide to Warfare'' Author's Cut &mdash; The Celestials|int=Star Wars: The Essential Guide to Warfare Author's Cut}}</ref> The [[Aing-Tii/Legends|Aing-Tii]] people in the [[Kathol Rift/Legends|Kathol Rift]] kept the Kathol [[Relics|relic]] known as the [[Codex]] that [[Darth Caedus|Jacen Solo]] and later Luke Skywalker used to detect the [[Disturbance in the Force/Legends|disturbance in the Force]] originating in [[Maw Cluster/Legends|the Maw]], in which Abeloth was imprisoned.<ref name="Omen">''[[Fate of the Jedi: Omen]]''</ref>

